criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult (≥ 18 years of age) patients;

          -  the presence of a confirmed pancreatic mass (suspected neoplastic) deemed resectable
             or borderline resectable on multislice (at least 16 simultaneously acquired slices)
             pancreatic protocol computed tomography (CT);

          -  patients fit and willing to undergo surgery with a curative (R0) intent;

          -  sign of the informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  the presence of significant co-morbidities that contraindicate pancreatic resection;

          -  previous neo-adjuvant oncologic therapy;

          -  distant metastases;

          -  lack of discernment;

          -  refusal to sign the informed consent..
